name: La Taberna del Pintxo Larios
formatted_address: Calle Alarc√≥n Luj√°n 12, Esq, C. Antonio Baena G√≥mez, n¬∫ 3, Distrito Centro, 29005 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text: Love this place, it's a buffet where all the food have a little stick in. You pay after you have eaten, they then count your sticks and tell you the bill. We liked all off it, then we saw the dessert buffet... we were full but we found our dessert stomach and had a little more to eat. Fun concept.

I really enjoyed this restaurant. It's a great concept of self service cold tapas at the bar and the lovely staff walk around with freshly cooked tapas, and explain what everything is and you can either say yes you want them or no!

The bill is calculated from the sticks that are attached to the tapas.
Really good value for money. I will go back!

I just love this place!
You can either sit at a table and wait for the waiters to come with tapas and ask you which one you want or you can go inside, take a plate and serve yourself. The price is calculated by the type of stick (look inside for the price).
For drinks, the water will bring you to the table.
Delicious food, great service and brilliant pricing idea!

Went to this place 3 days out of 4. Great food, very friendly, would definitely recommend. I‚Äôm terrible at taking of photos of food; the pork/mushroom sauce /balsamic was glorious. As was the prawn tartlette. Thank you x

I called in here for a few pintxos and a cool ca√±a on Sunday afternoon.

The selection is pretty impressive, with some tasty choices available from both the self-serve area as well as the hot pintxos being brought around straight from the kitchen (the fritter containing asparagus was beautiful!). The staff were helpful too. Will happily come back in.

name: Kraken Centro - Tapas Restaurant
formatted_address: Pl. de las Flores, 2, Distrito Centro, 29005 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text: Absolutely delicious experience! Every dish we tried was full of flavor and beautifully presented. The seafood was incredibly fresh, and the variety of tapas made it hard to choose ‚Äì in the best way possible! Cozy atmosphere, friendly service, and great value for money. Perfect spot with a local vibe. We‚Äôll definitely be back next time we‚Äôre in town!

The restaurant was nice as we walked in and we had high expectations because the reviews were pretty good for this place. The service provided by the staff and especially Marti has been excellent!

My only grip is that the food did not meet the expectations. I did enjoy the Cod, Cuttlefish & escalope.

I would like to note that we did not get any drinks.

Kraken has a nice interior and friendly service. There aren‚Äôt any fully vegan dishes on the menu, but it was no problem to leave out the mayo and cheese from the vegetarian options, which I appreciated.
We got fresh bread as a starter ‚Äî warm with a crispy crust. Everything was nicely presented.
Overall, a pleasant place for a relaxed meal.
A very special place! You can try to taste a twist of Spanish cuisine mix with a new breath üòÄ I do recommend the escallop- at least one to try and mini tacos with ship. I did enjoyed it ‚ò∫Ô∏è

The food was good I have to say. The place it's really lovely in the flowers square.
But for a change in Spain, we got the best service thanks to Ari. I wish waiters were like her, since Spanish service it's terrible.

name: Bar M√°laga
formatted_address: Calle Sta. Mar√≠a, 4, Distrito Centro, 29015 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text: This was a small bar/tapas place with pretty standard traditional selection of dishes. Everything we tried was pretty good, but heavy. Octopus was the only one that I didn‚Äôt like too much, it was a bit undercooked and not well seasoned. Their Flamenquin was one of the best ones we tried in our Spain trip. Portions are quite big as well.

Tucked away in the heart of Malaga‚Äôs Old Town, Bar Malaga is an absolute tip top gem; absolutely love this place.

Super friendly staff, amazing service, and that laid-back vibe that makes you want to stay all night. A perfect spot for good drinks, great company, and a proper Andalusian welcome.

We didn‚Äôt have reservations, but Gabriela got us a great private table with delicacy and smile, also reminded us to leave on the agreed time for the next guest. We had a great moment with a great suggested wine. Thanks Gabi.
A beautiful bar and restaurant with many old musical instruments. Their service is lovely as well as the tapas.

I was pleasantly surprised by the quality of food. Usually, you don't expect good food in the main tourist route. Fish was good and pork cheeks just amazing, melting in the mouth. And reasonably priced.

name: Antigua Casa de Guardia
formatted_address: Alameda Principal, 18, Distrito Centro, 29005 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text: No food for us however the experience was great. Our taxi driver suggested this spot as a unique Malaga experience. The wine, especially a 3 part blend they made for me was great and I'm not really a wine drinker. The space was tight and air warm but we still had conversations with 2 couples on their own holiday. It's a "should do" event for sure.

We had a really funny evening there. The staff and also the guests are funny and nice, just dont try to order Sangria üòÄ

I had some tapas which were also really good.

With some wine down its easy to make new friends there.
Sometimes musicians are playing in a corner, which elevates the good atmosphere in there even more.

Must visit when you are in Malaga.
Great place to taste vermouth and other local vines from barrels. A lot of atmosphere! Small tapas servings but focus is on the vine.

Had read about this place before spending a few days in M√°laga so a visit was on the list of things to do. What a great place! Buzzing atmosphere and packed! We left the choices of wines to the bar staff but had worked our way through them all by the time we left! Good value and well worth a visit

If you are looking for a unique place with the atmosphere of old Spain, be sure to visit this cafe in the center of Malaga! Its main highlight is the wine, which is poured directly from huge barrels. The selection is simply impressive: there is a drink for every taste, from light to rich varieties.

The atmosphere of the place is cozy and authentic, as if you are transported back in time. Delicious snacks are served with the wine, which perfectly complement the tasting.

Visiting this cafe is a real adventure and an opportunity to feel the spirit of Andalusia. I highly recommend it to everyone who loves wine and unusual places!

name: Ronda 14. Bar de tapas y restaurante fusi√≥n.
formatted_address: C. Luis de Vel√°zquez, 3, Distrito Centro, 29008 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text: We are big fans of Ronda 14 in Madrid, so we were eager to try the Malaga version, and we were not disappointed! One thing I wish is that the fried sweet potatoes on the rolls had been freshly fried; they seemed like they had been left out for too long, which slightly ruined the texture. Other than that, everything was perfect, and the service was amazing. We left with happy tummies. We would definitely come back!

Fusion restaurant serving Asturian-Peruvian-Japanese tapas. Very interesting flavours & tapas concept in general. We managed to try a bit of everything from the menu, all dishes looked great and tasted goodüëç

Stopped by this bustling corner spot, perfect for people-watching while enjoying some food and wine. I tried the beef meatballs, crackling pork with Creole salad, and Gyoza de Anticucho. All the dishes were flavorful, though the crackling pork leaned more toward meat than the crispy crackling I had hoped for.

We arrived to M√°laga during a very busy May weekend, wondering where we might find a good spot for food. After a short walk, we came across Ronda 14‚Äîa lively, stylish restaurant buzzing with people. It immediately caught our attention.

From the moment we stepped in, we were warmly welcomed by our amazing waitress, Ludmila. She looked after us from start to finish and made our entire experience truly memorable. Not being too familiar with the menu, we appreciated how she took the time to talk us through it, offering thoughtful recommendations and sharing her personal favourites.

Thanks to Ludmila's guidance and hospitality, our meal turned out to be absolutely brilliant. Her friendly and attentive service really made the evening special. Massive shout out to Ludmila‚Äîyou took such great care of us!

We‚Äôll definitely be back. Highly recommend Ronda 14 for anyone looking for great food and fantastic service in M√°laga

The food was absolutely lovely, very good quality tuna, and gorgeous ceviche. Such lovely wait staff. We were the only people there for a slightly late lunch but I'm not sure why because, it was a great dining experience!!

I was struggling to pick a white wine and the waitress brought me one to try after asking what kind of wine i like, and it was perfect and very reasonably priced.

name: LOLITA Taberna Andaluza
formatted_address: C. Granada, 17, Distrito Centro, 29015 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text:
The food was decent, but fell short of the average we experienced throughout our multi-city trip in Spain.

Service was good‚Äîfast and efficient.

The decor and atmosphere were outstanding, a perfect 10/10.

Walking around evening streets in Malaga and looking for some good place for tapas I found Lolita. I was nicely surprised by the size of the tapas portions, the staff was friendly and the atmosphere was good. They brought a bread as a starter and I didnt eat it, it was on the bill but when I claimed it the waiter with no problem removed it from the bill. Fair enough. Recommended!

We came in and it was raining, we were greeted with a warm smile. I requested to be seated near the outdoor heater and with a smile from the staff I was seated next to it.
The food was amazing and I usually don‚Äôt have dessert however the cheesecake was divine!
I highly recommend Lolita for the food and most especially the service from Renata and Hamada!

The worst food I‚Äôve had in Spain.
Seriously, I‚Äôve been to Spain 3 times, this time for a month.
The dish I ordered was called Crispy Chicken Cubes in Almond Sauce.
It‚Äôs was nice to sit outside but the ‚Äúcrispy chicken cubes‚Äù had no flavor at all, just old fried oil taste. it was  junk food without the salt and spices. I have no idea what the ‚Äúalmond sauce‚Äù was but it also had no taste. I think it was tinted Mayo. ü§∑
And the sauce portion was so small, service was bad so I couldn‚Äôt get more when it quickly ran out - they totally ignore you. And to make things worse, one of the food servers tool a break to clean the toilets!! Seriously!
I went to use the toilet and he blocked off the bathroom door with chairs, he said it would only take him 5 min to clean the bathroom! üò≤
You can‚Äôt make this stuff up!!

We ordered the broken eggs with ham and they were fantastic! We also ordered some tapas and were a bit disappointed since it didn‚Äôt match the picture in the menu and the sauce wasn‚Äôt on the side but underneath the omelette. The croquettes were nice.

name: Casa Lola
formatted_address: C. Granada, 46, Distrito Centro, 29015 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text: Very rarely I give in all aspects 5 stars. Even long queue in front of the restaurant is very well managed. They do not allow you inside to interfere guests. They ask you kindly to stay outside but take your name and really take care about it. Food and atmosphere inside is top. You feel quality on your tongue and this is very good experience. We loved it so much. Congratulations!

Absolutely love their good! Everything we ordered was really good and superb. I would definitely go back when I‚Äôm back in Malaga.

Would recommend the fish!

We very much enjoyed this tapas bar. An extensive and simple menu invites you to try a number of small wonderful  tapas.

We started with a Vermut. Nice size, well chilled and good quality. I love the fresh orange slice! Olives and bread were provided.

We had a lot of fun starting with tapas with shrimp with spicy mayo, brie and caramelized onions, quails eggs and chorizo, a small sandwich with seared pork...I will attach a picture of the receipt. The decor, energy and vibe of this place was amazing. We could have stayed all afternoon. The only nitpick I have is that the server seemed a bit impatient and slightly annoyed when we first arrived and we struggled with our Spanish. We have visited many tapas bars in Barcelona, Madrid and Seville and have found staff patient and helpful. This is a wonderful place so don't misunderstand. My overall rating would easily be a 5 if not for this. I think it's quite likely that this establishment gets a lot of tourists so their pa to fence may get tested. I highly highly recommend...it's a subtle remark.

The line gets so long around after 19:30 but they try to organize it in a timely manner. Extensive selection of tapas. The bar area is pretty nice. They charge you for bread even if you don‚Äôt eat it. Food was good.

This is, in my oppinion, an overhyped restaurant. The staff was good in organizing the crowd, but the waiters looked overworked. There is a big customer turnover and they do all the work.
The food was ok, nothing special, nothing to remember.
The place is very crowded and you don't have much room to stay. It was also very very loud inside, at the point of being exhausting.
The service was fast, but we needed to wait a little bit more for the check.
In my oppinion, you can skip this one for other better restaurants.

name: Uvedoble Taberna
formatted_address: C/ Alcazabilla, 1, Distrito Centro, 29015 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text:
This restaurant in the heart of M√°laga is exceptional. I was lucky enough to get a table outside around 3 PM, which was perfect for enjoying the sun.

My server was very attentive and helped me navigate the menu.

Although they had run out of sangria, I tried the summer red‚Äîa great alternative. It was fruity and full of bright, summery flavors.

The food was on another level. The garlic prawn mini-kebab and the crusty king prawn rolls with soy sauce were the highlights. The kebab was packed with juicy, fresh prawns, while the king prawn rolls‚Äîprawns wrapped in filo pastry and fried‚Äîwere simple yet executed to perfection.

I wasn‚Äôt the biggest fan of the black toasted noodles with M√°laga little squids. I found them lacking in flavor, and there weren‚Äôt many squid pieces. However, it was still an interesting dish to try.

Overall, this is a fantastic place to eat. It came highly recommended by a friend, and I can see why. I‚Äôve also tried visiting during peak lunch and dinner hours, but they get very busy. If you can, book a table in advance to avoid disappointment.

Despite looking like a tourist place due to its location, this is actually a place I would recommend going. Upscale tapas and larges dishes. The pulpo was terrific and so were the oxtail balls (although the fries were drenched in gravy), squid and brioche. However, vegetable options are limited.

Lovely little place, excellent tapas, friendly service and the waiter spoke good English. We had 5 small tapas and one medium dish. Our favourites included the ham croquettes, the blackened noodles with baby squid and the lamb couscous.

For just over ¬£50 including 3 beers and 2 aperol spritz, it was well worth every penny.

We went on a Tuesday night in early April, there were people waiting for tables from about 8:30 so it's well worth booking ahead through their website. Local guides also recommend this place.

Santiago is the absolute best. He fully picked all of our dishes from starter to the dessert. He completely took care of us. We absolutely loved our meal here. Wish it wasn‚Äôt the last night or else we would totally have come more than once this trip!!! Please try it! Incredible. Our favorite in Malaga!
Food was really tasty and modern Spanish tapas. Good value for money in city centre. The downside was the waiting time so it is really advisable that you book in advance.

name: Bar La Tranca
formatted_address: C. Carreter√≠a, 92, Distrito Centro, 29008 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text: I absolutely loved this place! We were staying right up the street and had brunch here 2 days in a row. The food was super super good, we tried a bunch of things. The shrimp skewers, the piemento de padron, tortilla, flamequin, empanadas, all of it, delicious! The drinks too! The atmosphere seemed very authentic, very little English was spoken but we understood each other. Highly recommend!

We absolutely loved this place, if atmosphere is everything then this has it in bucketloads. We were made welcomed instantly, barman called over and pointed to seats. We feasted on the tapas in front of us and sampled beer and vermouth all served instantly by the attentive staff. At the end of the night they tot up the bill in chalk directly on the wooden bar. Cool touch. Loved it. A real highlight.

Authentic tapas bar with delicious drinks and (obviously) tapas. Everything we ordered tasted amazing! We loved the vibe so much that we came back two nights in a row! Seemed to be a local favorite as well. I wish they had an English Menu though - still working on my Spanish.

Absolutely in love with this place. Very colourful and full of ambiance, tasty tapas, friendly personnel and reasonable prices. Calculating the bill with chalk on the counter is a very charming touch. Would warmly recommend whenever you go to Malaga

Very authentic in a sea of tourist places. Small ,packed with nice selection of tapas.  Prices are  very good. 3 large tapas including snails plus 2 large beers and sparkling water ‚Ç¨13.50.  arrive early or expect to stand.

name: Restaurante Esquina Granada
formatted_address: C. Granada, 73, Distrito Centro, 29015 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text: Trust me when I say, that you don‚Äôt want to skip this place. My first visit to Spain, my first day and I just happened to be passing through the Calle Granada when I spotted this restaurant. It had some sort of wonderful spell to it. I looked at the menu, liking its contents and waited 5 minutes for them to fully open the restaurant. Eager to try the traditional cuisine I ordered gazpacho and needless to say, I was not disappointed. In fact I enjoyed it very much. The main course, the fried baby squids, was absolutely divine. The staff was very kind, swift and very friendly. I ended up returning two more times to this lovely place during my stay, never missing a chance to try some of their delicious tapas. This place was the greatest introduction to the Spanish cuisine I could ever wish for. I wish them luck and hope that other visitors of Malaga will find their way to this place as well.

A wonderful place, highly recommended! We had the seafood paella and Catalan cream ‚Äî both were incredibly delicious. I especially want to highlight the staff: friendly, smiling, and very attentive ‚Äî the service was excellent. The atmosphere was cozy and pleasant. I‚Äôll definitely come back again!

I really enjoyed this restaurant, I only had tapas but they were excellent . I highly recommend the mussels they were slightly spicy but delicious. The prices were more than reasonable. I would definitely come back.

really great & friendly service! checked in on us throughout our meal. the food was pretty good and decent as well.

thoroughly enjoyed the gazpacho (cold tomato soup) cos the weather was HOT ü•µ

the iberian pork cheeks were so yummy and tender, the sauce was rly rly good‚Äîa balanced mix of savoury, tangy & slightly spicy/peppery idk what it is but it went so well with everything in the dish.

had their seafood paella too (much worth to get 2 pax for 25‚Ç¨ as compared to 1 pax for 17‚Ç¨), very big portions, quite a lot of seafood but didnt have squid :(

this place was a good find, and made for a peaceful mealtime amidst the hustle and busyle of the busy town centre üëç

Saw that this restaurant had great reviews, but we were honestly so disappointed by the food. It felt like a tourist trap. The batatas bravas were hard and tasteless, the paella tasted like a tourist version and the croquettes were also not anything special. We ended up not finishing the paella. The tuna tartare was okay and the sangria was good. The staff were nice, but perhaps a bit busy and not always remembering what we asked for.

name: Cortijo de Pepe
formatted_address: Pl. de la Merced, 2, Distrito Centro, 29012 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text:
One of the best place that we‚Äôve tried in Malaga. We even got back on the last night and tried again the grilled octopus. Super delicious, everything was just perfect.
Prices are also decent, even lower compared to many other places in the city centre.
The personal was a bit slow on the last night but they were friendly.
Very recommended!

I saw a review on social media saying that here they had the best tapas in Malaga. Honestly the food is good but nothing out of the ordinary. Nothing that you wouldn‚Äôt find in any tapas restaurant around the neighborhood. However the service is amazing and the ambience is cool. It worth a visit but don‚Äôt create high expectations.

The service is a bit slow even we went very early and there were a lot of empty table. We expect it to be amazing due to great reviews on Google but turned out the food is just average. Shrimp is a bit oily where oxtail is smelly. My favourite part is potatoes! They are tender and well-seasoned

Atmosphere is not good because we were seated outside where the homeless man was yelling very loudly and ruined the whole vibe. This is not restaurant fault but still really annoying. You would want to sit outside on a summer day

Visited twice. Busy place but with superb service.
Typical Spanish menu
Possibly the best pork I've ever eaten from the charcoal grill.
Highly recommended

The food was amazing specially the grilled octopus. The prices are nice and the options too many . We really enjoyed our time there, only problem the dishes came in much time between them, some of us had to either finish their food or eat it cold waiting for the others to be served. Also we found it a bit hard to get the attention of not the most friendly waitress. The toilets also aren't a plus...

name: Tasca La Salita
formatted_address: C. Mariblanca, 10, Distrito Centro, 29012 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text: Quite good place with reasonable prices. I personally didn‚Äôt like some of the tapas we ordered, and the tables felt dirty and sticky

The vintage ambiance makes it feel like time has stopped in the past. The place offers a fantastic assortment of tapas, all of which are delicious. I personally loved the boquerones and chorizos a la sidra. Please note that the seating consists of stools, so don‚Äôt expect a traditional restaurant setting. Instead, it‚Äôs more of a casual spot perfect for gathering with friends and having a great time. The waitress was very professional.
Highly recommended. Have been here a few times over the past few years. Expect lots of locals, genuine Spanish food, wine and beers. Plus some of the most friendly owners serving you.

I don't like writing bad reviews, but I really don't understand how this place has a 4.7 score. The tapas are very bland. We took five of them, one was nice, the other one was ok and the other three were tasteless. All of them were heated in the microwave in front of us. The price for what we got was more expensive than any other place. We've been to multiple tapas bars in M√°laga, this was the only one that I think was bad - all the others were really nice.

We lunch here two (2) times during our four (4) day stay in Malaga. The concept is like you‚Äôre in your mother‚Äôs living room eating home made food. We go here with locals friends and Chef Carlos brings whatever tapas he recommends. We tried the Fresh anchovies in vinegar
(Boquerones en vinagre), Mussels
(Mejillones), Grilled prawns (Gambas), Baby beans with iberian ham (Habitas con Jam√≥n), Stewed pork cheek with mushrooms (Carrillada con champi√±ones), Fried Fish tenders and a tasty Cabbage stew. For desert the Cheese Cake with Turr√≥n ice cream and the Orange cake both are excellent. Go with friends and order at least one tapa per person and share, around 12-15‚Ç¨/person with drinks.

name: Picasso Bar Tapas
formatted_address: Pl. de la Merced, 20, Distrito Centro, 29012 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text: The food was absolutely delicious. The waiters were incredibly kind and welcoming ‚Äì and not only that, they were also the most handsome I‚Äôve seen anywhere! The atmosphere? Out of this world. And the food‚Ä¶ Oh my God. It was something truly amazing. I usually don‚Äôt even enjoy eating, but here‚Ä¶ I could eat every single day!

Everything was absolutely delicious, and the staff were incredibly friendly and attentive. We also ordered a jar of sangria, which was just as fantastic as the food. The experience was top-notch, and I‚Äôll definitely be returning. A big thank you to the staff for the amazing food and outstanding service!

What an absolute gem this venue is! Not only is the food amazing but the atmosphere is everything you want and expect when your sat outdoor on the terrace watching the hustle and bustle that is Malaga ebb and flow past your table, from street dancers to singers, this place has it all. The location is perfect!
The food was also amazing!! In our 5 days visit too the city we ate 4 times here and everything we ate was 5*! For less the ‚Ç¨20 you can choose 5 Tapas plates from a wide selection of authentic Spanish food inc, the best chorizo cooked in cider iv ever tasted! Slow cooked Spanish beef stew, üòã was out of this world flavour wise! Fried fish, squid, prawns, octopus they have the lot and all of was divine!! I think what truly completes the experience is the staff, the waiters are amazing at the job, the orchestrate the balcony with ease, always attended too, and a joy to watch how they charm every table with ease. Your made to feel special ‚ú®Ô∏è  our waiters Crawford from Wales but has lived in malaga for 20 years was exceptionally good at his job, we both really enjoyed watching him do his job,  pulling groups of customers in off the street to dine using his charm in multiple languages was class! Not doubt this all adds to the atmosphere of Tapas on a busy square in a busy Spanish city eating lunch,  in the sun with a jug of sangria üòÄ  take me back!!! We miss it already!

Very fast service, large portions, and prices that are low considering the location and portion sizes. A big plus was that the kids enjoyed everything. The staff was very good and attentive.
We ordered the highly recommended "Mixed Tapas" (5 tapas) and the "Fritura Malague√±a." The dishes were very large but tasted just average. The quality was simply good, but it would be nice to have more vegetables and sauces.
Despite the restaurant being full, the waiting time was very short.
We might come back to try something else from the menu ‚Äî sometimes what people recommend isn't necessarily the best.
Crawford was the absolute BEST!!!! Food was  amazing. Gabriel was also so kind. Food was extremely fresh, came very quick and was delicious! We will definitely be back. Very affordable too

name: Tasca l√°ska
formatted_address: Av. de la Aurora, 1, Distrito Centro, 29002 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text: Everything was spotless! The food is just mind blowing, had the pork brioche and the oxtail croquetas and I couldn‚Äôt recommend more. The atmosphere is great, with nice music on the back, the girls servicing us were so gentle and nice. Defo a 5 stars!

Excellent food, atmosphere and everything else. The team were considerate, were attentive and friendly. Would highly recommended. It was busy so please book in advance. Highly recommend the tapas options, specifically the mushroom brioche (even if you don‚Äôt like mushrooms) and Patata brava.

I had an incredible experience at this restaurant! From the moment we arrived, Tobias was fantastic, guiding us through the menu and highlighting the best dishes. Daniel was also very friendly and went out of his way to be helpful. We can't forget about Paula, whose vibrant energy and outstanding customer service truly enhanced our dining experience. And of course, a huge shoutout to Chef Rafael, who prepared the most delicious food we've ever tasted in Spain. Having visited many cities and restaurants throughout the country, his exceptional culinary skills left a lasting impression on us!

6 stars for the food. Everything we ordered was a masterpiece, both in presentation and taste. The service is quite good too, and pricing very reasonable for the quality of the experience they provide. The food itself was not just food - it was an experience.
Top quality for a regular price. Incredible. Worth every penny twice over. Super highly recommended.

Great spot for well-presented tapas. Unlike traditional tapas dish, the restaurant offers creative options. Average price came to 25‚Ç¨ per person and the restaurant ambiance was ok with lots of space.

name: El Tapeo
formatted_address: C. H√©roe de Sostoa, 8, Distrito Centro, 29002 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text: A local cafe restaurant. We stopped by to have lunch and we were not disappointed. The food great, the fish very fresh and the prices very normal. The woman in the service was so fun to talk with. I am looking forward to go again.

We came here to eat with my wife who is pregnant and once we seated on the table we were told that it is for 4 people. Once we stend up they set two other peole there and we had to leave the place. Really bad experience! Dont go if you are not local!

Edit: we were offered the table and then we were told to stand up as they saw business opportunity with other group. Didnt respect the fact that my wife was pregnant and we belive it was very disrespectful! So themplace where we were seating was not reserved!

Great little place.
Really enjoyed my morning coffee and Moletto. Always served with a smile. Definitely recommend.
The food here is absolutely delicious. We tried most of the dishes and none failed the taste test
Excellent service!! Fantastic! Big portions.

name: Tapas Bar Ank√°
formatted_address: C. Cameros, Cruz de Humilladero, 29006 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text: Very well located next to the playground, you drink coffee and see the children, the road is very far away, the area is very safe. We will return without a doubt.

Prawns, mussels, razor clams, and very good.
Neighborhood bar but very good.

name: Big Tapas "El Pescaito"
formatted_address: C. de Alozaina, 1, Cruz de Humilladero, 29006 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text: Nice bar with nice servis. Good food and friendly stuff. Thanks
Good services and various delicious food
TOP
Just love it
Way

name: Restaurante Tapas y Fritos Dus
formatted_address: Cmo de S. Rafael, 36, Cruz de Humilladero, 29006 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text: Very kind lady and awesome asia food!
Nice food and the guy was very friendly. I had the chicken and rice and it was seasoned perfectly üëç

Recently, the place became Zhang Bar Restaurant. It offers various tapas and Asian food. We ordered chicken fried rice and beef noodles, and they were delicious. The sellers are also very friendly. Overall it was a great experience. I recommend them without a doubt! :)

Recently the place just changed to Bar Restaurant Zhang. It sells various tapas and asian food. We ordered the chicken fried rice and beef noodle and they are super delicious. The sellers are very very nice too. Great experience overall. I would definitely recommend them! :)
All 10, great warmth and cleanliness, kindness and unbeatable education. The delicious food. I ordered several times and everything was always perfect. I recommend. Varying dishes has many things.
Adequate price, especially the super cheap tapas, friendly service, if there is a problem, tell the waiter and they always solve it for you

name: Al punto - Tapas y brasas
formatted_address: C. Bodegueros, 28, Carretera de C√°diz, 29006 M√°laga, Spain

reviews.text: I really liked the variety they have on the menu, you can also opt for the menu of the day. Everything is great, to repeat!! In addition, they have a very nice terrace where you can choose sun or shade, I would definitely repeat. Attentive and fast service.

We went to play paddle tennis and stayed for dinner, it is a spectacular place with great quality food! We ordered several things to try and the best without a doubt were the mini burgers! Although everything was delicious! It is worth highlighting the treatment of the waiters and the attention. Carlos very friendly at all times! We will definitely return! It's a 10 out of 10!!

We booked a week before to celebrate a birthday and we were very well looked after and they helped us with all the preparations. Our little ones were on the grass playing (the enclosure is closed), they have two very comfortable high chairs and a changing table in the bathroom. The food was all very good and the place, all full of grass and how good the sun shines all day, TOP. We will repeat 100%.

An Oasis in the Neighborhood for the body and the stomach.
The Menu is extensive, they have tapas, portions and during the week, Menu of the day.
You can enjoy the terrace, on artificial grass, or inside, with an open space with lots of light and visibility provided by the lumon closure. We spent 3 PAX with my daughter and we ate very well for less than ‚Ç¨50.
To recommend and thus we convey to you the quality and quantity of the dishes. And especially for the croquettes, if you order the mix, try all three kinds: Boletus, Carridada and Ham.
The Wings, excellent, the Russian Salad, rich, soft and distinct, a fried egg on top, with shavings of ham.
Tenderloin tips, peppery with flavor and well-prepared meat.
Curry chicken to repeat, 3 chocolate cake, generous portion to share, special mention the price of the pint of San Miguel, ‚Ç¨2.50 and the coffee, delicious and very generous in quantity, not the espresso type.
Without a doubt we will repeat, in the neighborhood there is not much to choose from and with the given quality. Congratulations and the service and attention given.

Totally recommended, the staff is always very attentive if you need anything and the service is excellent. The food is very good and the place is beautiful. In addition, they have gluten-free beer, something that celiacs appreciate and that few places have. We will repeat a thousand times without hesitation!!

reviews.text: Had a great experience at this restaurant! The owner was incredibly friendly, and the whole place had such a warm and welcoming atmosphere. The service was excellent‚Äîeveryone was attentive and kind. The food was really good as well, and I‚Äôd definitely recommend it to anyone looking for a great meal in a friendly setting. Will be coming back for sure!

Excellent quality. Iberian pork, tomatoes with ventresca, delicious homemade croquettes... We come from Holland and will come back as soon as we can. There is a car park and a children's playground right in front. 100% recommended.

Well out of the way of anywhere, so mostly a place for local people, and we weren‚Äôt disappointed! The staff were super lovely and welcoming, the menu and food superb - and so cheap it was embarrassing when the bill came. Would go back in a heartbeat!
Decent food, great staff, and reasonable prices. They were also very patient with my terrible Spanish, which I appreciated.
Local place, if you near by stop and try really good food.
